Kako izvještava The Wall Street Journal, koji je objavio popis gradova kroz koje će protutnjati Beyonce na svojoj europskoj turneji, na samom vrhu, kao polazna točka nalazi se Zagreb.

Koncert bi se trebao održati u novoizgrađenoj dvorani Arena, a nakon toga Beyonce kreće put Beča, nakon kojeg će uslijediti koncerti u Budimpešti, Pragu i još 17 gradova, od kojih će zadnji biti u Belfastu u Odyssey Areni.

event.title: Essence Music Festival

artists.artist: Sharon Jones and the Dap Kings

event.description:
NEW YORK (Billboard) - MAXWELL, Anita Baker, Al Green and Ne-Yo will
join previously announced headliner Beyonce at the 15th annual Essence Music Festival this summer in New Orleans.

Also added to the lineup are John Legend, Robin Thicke, Salt-N-Pepa and En Vogue.

Organized by Essence magazine, the event is scheduled for July 3-5 at the New Orleans Superdome.

Rounding out the bill are Sierra Leone Refugee All Stars, Teena Marie, Eric Benet, Jazmine Sullivan, Janelle Monae, Raphael Saadiq, Sharon Jones and the Dap Kings, Zap Mama, The Knux, Irvin Mayfield, Lalah Hathaway, Blind Boys of Alabama, Ledisi, Marva Wright, Big Sam's Funky Nation, Brand New Heavies, Dan Dyer, DJ Soul Sister, Keri Hilson, Preservation Hall Jazz Band, Rebirth Brass Band, Trombone Shorty and Orleans Ave.

In addition to its concerts, the Essence festival is known for its empowerment seminars, which are free and open to ticket-holders on a first-come, first-served basis. Among the personalities participating in these events are Bill Cosby, Sheryl Lee Ralph, Donna Brazile, Tom Joyner, Hill Harper and Donnie McClurkin.

This year's festival also will include a tribute to pastor/author T.D. Jakes featuring CeCe Winans and Marvin Sapp, among others.

***************

Celebrate the 15th Anniversary of the ESSENCE Music Festival, July 3–5, 2009, in New Orleans, LA. It's the Ultimate Party Weekend with live musical performances each night, including Beyoncé, Maxwell, Anita Baker, John Legend with many more. The weekend also includes three days of Empowering Seminars FREE at the Convention Center with power speakers including Bishop T.D. Jakes, Dr. Juanita Bynum, Roland Martin, Tom Joyner and many more. Tickets are on sale now through Ticketmaster with the Best Prices.

Get a 15% discount on tickets purchased now through February 15, 2009.

You must buy a ticket for all three nights to get the 15% discount. No discount available for floor or Gold Circle tickets. Any additional service charges will be added after the discount has been calculated. All talent and programming is subject to change.
